  "summary": "triage-bot preinstall exfiltrates host data and /etc/passwd to oastify.com Collaborator host",
  "details": "package.json declares `preinstall: node index.js`, so `npm install triage-bot` automatically executes index.js. The script imports os, fs, and https and collects installer-side data — os.hostname(), os.userInfo(), home directory, DNS servers, current working directory — together with the contents of /etc/passwd and /etc/hosts, then POSTs the result over HTTPS to a Burp Collaborator subdomain (93asqi08lutl0joxvlv9v0rwknqee62v.oastify.com). The package has empty author and description fields and provides no functionality beyond this beacon, consistent with a dependency-confusion / namespace-takeover recon probe against internal package names.",
